<p>Minneapolis residents face some of the most challenging climate conditions in the United States, with winter temperatures regularly dropping below -10¬∞F and summer highs reaching into the 90s. This extreme temperature range puts significant demands on HVAC systems, requiring robust heating capabilities that can handle prolonged cold spells while still providing efficient cooling during hot, humid summers. The city's 429,954 residents in Hennepin County rely heavily on their heating systems for up to 7 months of the year, making energy efficiency a critical consideration for both comfort and cost management.</p>

